'''Óscar Cruz López''' (born 1 December 1957) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] politician affiliated with the [[Party of the Democratic Revolution]]. As of 2014 he served as Senator of the [[LIX Legislature of the Mexican Congress]] representing [[Oaxaca]] as replacement of [[Daniel López Nelio]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfil del legislador|url=http://sil.gobernacion.gob.mx/Librerias/pp_PerfilLegislador.php?SID=&Referencia=1097973|publisher=Legislative Information System|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

